# Explicit Independent Set Data for C₇^{⊠5}

367 vertices forming an independent set in C₇^{⊠5}, obtained via nondeterministic
rounding from the orbit {t·(1,7,49,343,109) : t ∈ ℤ₃₈₂} in E_{382/108}^{⊠5}
followed by ILP optimization (Gurobi). This gives Θ(C₇) ≥ 367^{1/5} ≈ 3.258.

The bound α(C₇^{⊠5}) ≥ 367 is due to Polak and Schrijver (2019).

## Encoding

Each vertex (a,b,c,d,e) ∈ (ℤ/7ℤ)⁵ is stored as a·2401 + b·343 + c·49 + d·7 + e.
The function `decodeVertex` recovers the 5-tuple from this encoding.
-/
import Mathlib.Data.ZMod.Basic

namespace C7Data

/-- Decode a base-7 encoded natural number to a vertex in (ZMod 7)^5. -/
def decodeVertex (n : ℕ) : Fin 5 → ZMod 7 :=
  fun i => match i with
    | 0 => (n / 2401 : ℕ)
    | 1 => (n / 343 % 7 : ℕ)
    | 2 => (n / 49 % 7 : ℕ)
    | 3 => (n / 7 % 7 : ℕ)
    | 4 => (n % 7 : ℕ)

